organization.description:
The City of Sydney is the local government authority responsible for the city centre and more than 30 suburbs within our boundaries. 

We have defined 10 village precincts, each with its own unique character. The area we look after covers 26.15 square kilometres extending from Sydney Harbour in the north, to Glebe and Camperdown in the west, and from Sydney Park and Rosebery in the south to Moore Park and Darlinghurst in the east.

The City provides essential local services such as our network of libraries, street cleansing, maintaining roads, assessing development applications, collecting waste and recycling, maintaining our parks, playgrounds, gardens, sports venues and community centres. On any given day, including the city's visitors, the City hosts 1 million people.

results.name: city-of-sydney-gpc-reports
results.notes:
## GPC Carbon inventory 2005_06
City of Sydney’s carbon inventory estimates for the baseline year 2014_2015 based on Global Protocol for Community-Scale Greenhouse Gas Emission Inventories (GPC).

The City of Sydney is compliant with international reporting standards such as the Compact of Mayors, CDP and C40, and has committed to working with cities across the globe to use consistent best practices in GHG emissions accounting. As a result, the City estimates its community-wide GHG emissions using the GPC Protocol.

## GHG emissions factors 2005_06
Emissions factors used to calculate GHG emissions from all the activities included in the City’s 2005_06 carbon inventory.
